Lending at Czech Building Societies Falls 28%, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-07-15T06:34:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/lending-at-czech-building-societies-falls-28-hospodarske-says.html
Lending at Czech building societies
fell 28 percent to 22 billion koruna ($1.27 billion) in the
first half of 2011 from a year earlier,  Hospodarske Noviny 
reported, citing data from the Czech building and loan
association.  The volume of such lending is the lowest since 2005, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  